         <abstract>
            <p>This note investigates a capital budgeting model based on multiple, expansible investment projects and economies of scale in average flotation costs (i.e., flotation costs per dollar of funds raised). The analysis reveals that independent projects become interdependent with respect to the scale of investment when financed with external capital subject to decreasing average flotation costs. Accordingly, managerial decisions regarding these projects must be made jointly. Flotation costs cannot be allocated to particular projects, only to the combined capital budget.</p>
         </abstract>
